cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with analyzing data from social media, specifically Twitter, and comparing the data obtained from the Streaming API with the full Firehose stream. This involves statistical analysis and comparison of topics, networks, and locations of tweets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for analyzing the tweets, making these sub-categories also likely.
